net.kuujo.copycat.raft

Interface Command<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Operation<T>, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Filter.All

    public interface Command<T>
extends Operation<T>
    Raft state commands modify system state.

    Commands are submitted by clients to a Raft instance and used to modify Raft cluster-wide state. The Raft consensus protocol dictates that commands must be forwarded to the cluster leader and replicated to a majority of followers before being applied to the cluster state. Thus, in contrast to queries, commands are not dictated by different consistency levels.

    Author:
    Jordan Halterman
